## 1. Product Overview

### 1.1 Purpose
A smart dehumidifier controller system built on ESP32-S2 that replaces broken control boards in dehumidifiers. The system provides local and remote monitoring/control capabilities with a TFT display interface and web-based configuration.

### 1.2 Target Hardware
- **Primary Platform**: Adafruit ESP32-S2 TFT Feather
- **Display**: Built-in 240x135 TFT display
- **Sensors**: Adafruit Sensirion SHT40 or SHTC3 temperature/humidity sensor (auto-detected)
- **Inputs**: Built-in BOOT button (GPIO 0), configurable float switch pin, configurable compressor relay pin
- **Outputs**: Configurable relay control pin, NeoPixel status LED

### 1.3 Key Features
- Real-time humidity and temperature monitoring
- Automatic dehumidifier control based on configurable target humidity
- Local control via BOOT button
- Web-based configuration and monitoring
- Captive portal WiFi setup
- Over-the-Air (OTA) firmware updates
- Optional Home Assistant integration via MQTT
- Visual status indicators (TFT display + NeoPixel LED)
- Compressor cooldown protection (5-minute minimum off time)
- Condensate tank monitoring via float switch

## 2. Functional Requirements

### 2.1 Core Control Logic

#### 2.1.1 Humidity Control
- **FR-001**: System shall maintain humidity within ±1% of target humidity setting
- **FR-002**: Target humidity range: 30-70% in 5% increments
- **FR-003**: System shall automatically start compressor when humidity exceeds (target + 1%)
- **FR-004**: System shall automatically stop compressor when humidity falls below target
- **FR-005**: Target humidity setting shall persist across power cycles (stored in EEPROM)

#### 2.1.2 Compressor Protection
- **FR-006**: System shall enforce minimum 5-minute cooldown period between compressor cycles
- **FR-007**: Cooldown state shall persist across power cycles (stored in EEPROM)
- **FR-008**: System shall display "COOL" status during cooldown period
- **FR-009**: System shall prevent compressor start during cooldown period

#### 2.1.3 Safety Features
- **FR-010**: System shall immediately stop compressor when float switch indicates full tank
- **FR-011**: System shall display "FULL" warning when tank is full
- **FR-012**: System shall prevent compressor operation while tank is full
- **FR-013**: System shall continue operating even if sensors are not detected (graceful degradation)

### 2.2 User Interface

#### 2.2.1 TFT Display
- **FR-014**: Display shall show current humidity in large, readable format (18pt font)
- **FR-015**: Display shall show target humidity setting
- **FR-016**: Display shall show temperature in both Celsius and Fahrenheit
- **FR-017**: Display shall show IP address (or AP mode indicator)
- **FR-018**: Display shall update at 200Hz refresh rate for smooth animations
- **FR-019**: Display shall show status bar with:
  - Tank level status (OK/FULL)
  - Relay status (ON/OFF/COOL)
  - WiFi connection status with signal strength bars
- **FR-020**: Display shall show startup animation on boot
- **FR-021**: Display shall show status messages during initialization
- **FR-022**: Display shall show WiFi setup information when in AP mode

#### 2.2.2 Button Control
- **FR-023**: BOOT button press shall increment target humidity by 5%
- **FR-024**: Target humidity shall wrap from 70% to 30% when incremented beyond maximum
- **FR-025**: Button shall have 50ms debounce time
- **FR-026**: Target humidity changes shall be saved immediately to EEPROM

#### 2.2.3 NeoPixel Status LED
- **FR-027**: LED shall show green pulsing when compressor is running
- **FR-028**: LED shall show red pulsing when tank is full
- **FR-029**: LED shall show green fading when compressor is off and tank is OK
- **FR-030**: LED brightness shall be set to 50 (out of 255)

### 2.3 WiFi and Network

#### 2.3.1 WiFi Connection
- **FR-031**: System shall attempt to connect to configured WiFi network on startup
- **FR-032**: System shall store WiFi credentials in EEPROM
- **FR-033**: System shall attempt WiFi reconnection every 5 seconds if disconnected
- **FR-034**: System shall enter AP mode if WiFi connection fails
- **FR-035**: System shall display WiFi signal strength as 4-level bar indicator
- **FR-036**: System shall display RSSI value next to signal bars

#### 2.3.2 Access Point Mode
- **FR-037**: System shall create WiFi AP with SSID "Dehumidifier-Setup" when connection fails
- **FR-038**: AP password shall be "setup12345"
- **FR-039**: System shall implement captive portal (DNS server) to auto-open config page
- **FR-040**: System shall support captive portal detection for Android, iOS, Windows, and Kindle
- **FR-041**: System shall display AP SSID, password, and IP address on TFT display
- **FR-042**: System shall redirect all HTTP requests to WiFi config page when in AP mode

#### 2.3.3 Web Server
- **FR-043**: System shall provide web interface on port 80
- **FR-044**: Web interface shall display:
  - Current humidity and temperature
  - Target humidity setting
  - Compressor status
  - Tank status
  - Cooldown status
  - WiFi connection status
- **FR-045**: Web interface shall allow setting target humidity
- **FR-046**: Web interface shall provide JSON API endpoint at `/json`
- **FR-047**: Web interface shall provide firmware update page at `/update`
- **FR-048**: Web interface shall provide WiFi configuration page at `/wifi`

### 2.4 Configuration

#### 2.4.1 WiFi Configuration
- **FR-049**: System shall provide web-based WiFi credential configuration
- **FR-050**: Configuration page shall allow entering SSID and password
- **FR-051**: System shall validate SSID length (1-32 characters)
- **FR-052**: System shall attempt connection after saving WiFi credentials
- **FR-053**: System shall restart after successful WiFi connection

#### 2.4.2 Pin Configuration
- **FR-054**: System shall allow configuration of float switch pin via web UI
- **FR-055**: System shall allow configuration of compressor relay pin via web UI
- **FR-056**: Pin configuration shall be validated (0-48, must be different)
- **FR-057**: Pin configuration shall persist in EEPROM
- **FR-058**: System shall restart after pin configuration changes
- **FR-059**: Default pins: GPIO 12 (float switch), GPIO 13 (compressor relay)

### 2.5 Firmware Updates

#### 2.5.1 Over-the-Air Updates
- **FR-060**: System shall support OTA firmware updates via web interface
- **FR-061**: OTA updates shall only work when connected to WiFi (not in AP mode)
- **FR-062**: System shall display update progress on TFT display
- **FR-063**: System shall display update success/failure messages
- **FR-064**: System shall restart automatically after successful update
- **FR-065**: System shall timeout updates after 5 minutes

### 2.6 Sensor Management

#### 2.6.1 Sensor Detection
- **FR-066**: System shall auto-detect SHT4x sensor if connected
- **FR-067**: System shall auto-detect SHTC3 sensor if SHT4x not found
- **FR-068**: System shall continue operation if no sensor detected (graceful degradation)
- **FR-069**: System shall read sensors every 2 seconds
- **FR-070**: System shall display sensor initialization status during boot

### 2.7 Home Assistant Integration (Optional)

#### 2.7.1 MQTT Integration
- **FR-071**: System shall support MQTT integration when `ENABLE_HOME_ASSISTANT` is true
- **FR-072**: System shall publish device state every 5 seconds
- **FR-073**: System shall support Home Assistant auto-discovery
- **FR-074**: System shall subscribe to command topic for remote control
- **FR-075**: System shall publish availability status
- **FR-076**: System shall attempt MQTT reconnection every 5 seconds if disconnected

## 3. Non-Functional Requirements

### 3.1 Performance
- **NFR-001**: Display updates shall occur at 200Hz (5ms interval)
- **NFR-002**: Sensor readings shall occur every 2 seconds
- **NFR-003**: Status bar updates shall occur every 1 second
- **NFR-004**: Web server shall respond to requests within 100ms
- **NFR-005**: System shall use less than 40% of available program storage
- **NFR-006**: System shall use less than 25% of available dynamic memory

### 3.2 Reliability
- **NFR-007**: System shall recover from WiFi disconnections automatically
- **NFR-008**: System shall recover from sensor failures gracefully
- **NFR-009**: System shall persist critical state across power cycles
- **NFR-010**: System shall not hang during initialization if sensors are missing

### 3.3 Usability
- **NFR-011**: Display shall be readable from 2-3 feet away
- **NFR-012**: Status indicators shall be color-coded for quick recognition
- **NFR-013**: Web interface shall be mobile-responsive
- **NFR-014**: Configuration shall be intuitive and require minimal technical knowledge
- **NFR-015**: Captive portal shall auto-open on mobile devices

### 3.4 Maintainability
- **NFR-016**: Code shall be modular with clear separation of concerns
- **NFR-017**: Configuration shall be centralized in config.h
- **NFR-018**: System shall support OTA updates for easy maintenance
- **NFR-019**: Code shall follow Arduino/ESP32 best practices

## 4. Technical Specifications

### 4.1 Hardware Interfaces
- **GPIO 0**: BOOT button input (INPUT_PULLUP)
- **GPIO 7**: TFT CS
- **GPIO 12**: Default float switch input (INPUT_PULLUP, configurable)
- **GPIO 13**: Default compressor relay output (OUTPUT, configurable)
- **GPIO 21**: TFT I2C power
- **GPIO 39**: TFT DC
- **GPIO 40**: TFT RST
- **GPIO 45**: TFT backlight
- **GPIO 1**: NeoPixel data
- **I2C**: Sensor connection (SHT4x/SHTC3)

### 4.2 Data Storage (EEPROM)
- **Address 0-3**: Target humidity (float)
- **Address 4-7**: Last compressor off timestamp (unsigned long)
- **Address 8**: Compressor cooldown flag (bool)
- **Address 16-47**: WiFi SSID (32 bytes)
- **Address 48-111**: WiFi password (64 bytes)
- **Address 112**: WiFi credentials valid flag (byte)
- **Address 113**: Float switch pin (byte)
- **Address 114**: Compressor relay pin (byte)
- **Address 115**: Pin configuration valid flag (byte)

### 4.3 Network Protocols
- **HTTP**: Port 80 for web interface
- **DNS**: Port 53 for captive portal
- **MQTT**: Port 1883 (when Home Assistant enabled)
- **OTA**: Port 3232 (ArduinoOTA default)

### 4.4 Timing Constants
- Sensor read interval: 2000ms
- Display update interval: 5ms
- Status bar update interval: 1000ms
- WiFi reconnect interval: 5000ms
- Compressor minimum off time: 300000ms (5 minutes)
- Button debounce time: 50ms

## 5. User Stories

### 5.1 As a homeowner
- I want to control my dehumidifier remotely so I can adjust settings without going to the basement
- I want to see current humidity levels so I know if the dehumidifier is working
- I want the system to automatically control the dehumidifier so I don't have to manually turn it on/off
- I want to be notified when the tank is full so I can empty it before it overflows

### 5.2 As a technician
- I want to configure WiFi credentials easily so I can set up the device quickly
- I want to configure pin assignments so I can adapt to different hardware configurations
- I want to update firmware remotely so I don't have to physically access the device
- I want to see detailed status information so I can troubleshoot issues

### 5.3 As a smart home user
- I want to integrate with Home Assistant so I can control the dehumidifier from my home automation system
- I want to see humidity trends so I can optimize my home's climate control
- I want to receive alerts when the tank is full so I can empty it promptly

## 6. Constraints and Assumptions

### 6.1 Constraints
- ESP32-S2 has limited GPIO pins (must be configurable)
- EEPROM size is limited to 512 bytes
- Display resolution is fixed at 240x135 pixels
- Compressor requires minimum 5-minute cooldown period
- WiFi range is limited by ESP32-S2 radio capabilities

### 6.2 Assumptions
- User has basic WiFi network knowledge
- User has access to a computer or mobile device for initial setup
- Dehumidifier has a standard relay control interface
- Float switch is normally-open and closes when tank is full
- Power supply is stable and adequate for ESP32-S2 and relay

## 7. Future Enhancements

### 7.1 Potential Features
- Scheduled operation (time-based control)
- Humidity history logging
