- Advanced sensor calibration options
- Power consumption optimization

## 8. Documentation Maintenance

### 8.1 Documentation Synchronization Requirements

**CRITICAL**: The PRD (`prd.mdc`) and README (`README.md`) must be kept synchronized with the codebase at all times.

#### 8.1.1 When Documentation Must Be Updated

Documentation must be updated whenever any of the following changes occur:

- **Feature Changes**: Any new features, removed features, or modified functionality
- **Hardware Changes**: Pin assignments, hardware requirements, or supported hardware
- **Configuration Changes**: New configuration options, EEPROM layout changes, or default values
- **API Changes**: New endpoints, changed endpoints, or modified JSON responses
- **Protocol Changes**: WiFi settings, MQTT topics, or network protocols
- **UI Changes**: Display layout, web interface changes, or user interaction changes
- **Version Updates**: Any version number changes or release notes

#### 8.1.2 Documentation Update Checklist

When making code changes, ensure the following are updated:

**PRD Updates Required:**
- [ ] Functional Requirements (FR-XXX) - Add/modify/remove as needed
- [ ] Non-Functional Requirements (NFR-XXX) - Update performance, reliability, usability specs
- [ ] Technical Specifications - Update hardware interfaces, EEPROM layout, protocols, timing
- [ ] User Stories - Add new user stories if new use cases are introduced
- [ ] Version History - Document changes in new version entry

**README Updates Required:**
- [ ] Hardware Requirements - Update if new hardware is required
- [ ] Pin Connections - Update if pin assignments change
- [ ] Software Setup - Update installation instructions if dependencies change
- [ ] Features List - Add/remove features as they change
- [ ] Display Features - Update if display layout or information changes
- [ ] Web Interface - Update endpoints, features, or usage instructions
- [ ] Configuration Instructions - Update if configuration process changes
- [ ] Troubleshooting - Add new issues/solutions as discovered

#### 8.1.3 Synchronization Points

The following sections must match between PRD and README:

| PRD Section | README Section | Sync Requirement |
|------------|----------------|------------------|
| 1.2 Target Hardware | Hardware Requirements | Must match exactly |
| 4.1 Hardware Interfaces | Pin Connections | Must match exactly |
| 2.3.2 Access Point Mode | WiFi Setup | Must match SSID/password |
| 2.4.2 Pin Configuration | Pin Connections | Must match default pins |
| 2.5.1 OTA Updates | OTA Updates | Must match process |
| 2.7.1 MQTT Integration | Home Assistant Integration | Must match topics/settings |
| 2.2.1 TFT Display | Display Features | Must match capabilities |
| 2.3.3 Web Server | Web Interface | Must match endpoints |

#### 8.1.4 Documentation Maintenance Process

1. **Before Making Code Changes:**
   - Review current PRD and README
   - Identify which sections will be affected
   - Plan documentation updates alongside code changes

2. **During Code Changes:**
   - Update code comments if functionality changes
   - Update inline documentation (function headers, etc.)
   - Note any breaking changes

3. **After Code Changes:**
   - Update PRD with new/modified requirements
   - Update README with new/modified instructions
   - Verify synchronization between PRD and README
   - Update version history in PRD
   - Test that documentation examples still work

4. **Before Release:**
   - Complete documentation review checklist
   - Verify all code examples in README are current
   - Ensure all feature lists are accurate
   - Check that troubleshooting section covers known issues
   - Verify version numbers match across all documents

#### 8.1.5 Documentation Standards

- **Accuracy**: All information must be accurate and testable
- **Completeness**: All features must be documented
- **Clarity**: Documentation must be clear and understandable
- **Examples**: Code examples must be current and functional
- **Consistency**: Terminology and formatting must be consistent
- **Currency**: Documentation must reflect current codebase state

#### 8.1.6 Automated Documentation Checks

Consider implementing:
- Pre-commit hooks to check for documentation updates
- CI/CD checks to verify PRD and README synchronization
- Automated generation of feature lists from code comments
- Version number consistency checks

#### 8.1.7 Documentation Review Schedule

- **Before each release**: Full documentation review
- **After major features**: Update relevant sections immediately
- **Monthly**: Review for accuracy and completeness
- **When bugs are fixed**: Update troubleshooting section if needed

